				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$EROI={\text{}}\frac{{{E_g}}}{{{E_c}+~{E_{op}}+~{E_d}}}$$\end{document}

In a prospective 100% VRE scenario, it is not necessary to consider the displaced capacity as shown in Fig. 7 since it is assumed that there is zero fossil fuel capacity. The system-wide EROIsystem is calculated as a standalone estimate for the given probabilistic reliability (e.g. LOLE = 0.1) as shown in Eq. 3, where EROIsystem is the ratio of the gross lifetime energy supplied by the entire system Eg, and the sum of the lifetime embodied energy of the VRE, EVRE and storage, Estorage.3EROIsystem=EgEVRE+Estorage\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
